<concept id="howto_multitenancy">
 <title>How To Create a Multitenant Enterprise Data Hub</title>
  <conbody>
  <p>Multitenancy in an enterprise data hub (EDH) lets you share the collective resources of your
   CDH clusters between user groups without impacting application performance or compromising
   security.</p>
   <p>
    Advantages of multitenancy include opportunities for data sharing, consolidated operations, improved performance, and better use of resources.
   </p>
   <p>For a more in-depth discussion of the rationale for multitenancy, see the whitepaper <xref
    href="https://www.cloudera.com/content/dam/cloudera/Resources/PDF/whitepaper/Multitenancy_and_the_Enterprise_Data_Hub.pdf"
    format="pdf" scope="external">Multitenancy and the Enterprise Data Hub</xref>.</p></conbody>
  <concept id="choosing_an_isolation_model"><title>Choosing an Isolation Model</title>
   <conbody><p>There are three
   standard isolation models for an EDH: Share Nothing, Share Management, Share Resources.</p></conbody></concept>
